The paper deals with topics related to computability, randomness, and information theory, which are typically covered in the sub-categories of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Information Theory (cs.IT), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper's focus on provability in Peano Arithmetic also suggests a connection to mathematical logic and proof theory, which is covered in cs.LO.
